        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Battlefield-6-Official-Reveal-Trailer-0-58-screenshot.png?width=570&amp;quality=80&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 2dppx)">
        
      </picture>

        <figcaption>
          <span>Image credit: <cite>EA</cite></span>
        </figcaption>
  </figure>
  </p>

    

</header>
    <div data-component="article-content">



            <p><a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/battlefield-2025">Battlefield 6</a> has rocketed into Steam's chart of the biggest-ever games, becoming Steam's fourteenth most-popular game of all time by concurrent user numbers on the PC platform within 24 hours of its launch.</p>
<p>Eclipsing even its own free-to-play open beta and Call of Duty's peak numbers, Battlefield 6 is now EA's most successful shooter ever after clocking up 747,440 concurrent players in a single day. And that's only counting Steam players, of course.</p>
